==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roseola
<hw>Ro*se"o*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., dim. of
L. <ets>rosa</ets> a rose.]</ety> <fld>(med.)</fld> <def>A rose-colored
efflorescence upon the skin, occurring in circumscribed patches of
little or no elevation and often alternately fading and reviving; also,
an acute specific disease which is characterized by an eruption of this
character; -- called also <altname>rose rash</altname>.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Ro*se"o*lous</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rose-pink</ent>⟦br⟧
